OL,3,CMan told 'we don't serve Protestants'
OL,4,Cin bar wins discrimination case
OL,6,FMr Bittles has apologised for any
OL,7,Fupset and distress caused to the man.
OL,9,FThe man said he was told told by Mr
OL,10,FBittles "you have not been in here for
OL,11,Fabout three years and we don't serve
OL,12,FProtestants, only joking, no I'm not".
OL,14,FHe took the case against the bar with
OL,15,Fsupport from the Equality Commission.
OL,17,FA statement from the commission
OL,18,Fexplained: "He was embarrassed and
OL,19,Ffelt intimidated by what happened.
